cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.MM, cs.HC, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) sub-category as it deals with facial expression recognition using 4D data. The use of deep learning and augmentation techniques also suggests that it could belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The use of multi-views and landmarks suggests that it could also belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Additionally, the focus on facial expressions suggests that it could belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category. Finally, the use of long short-term memory (LSTM) networks suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
